language Essence 1.3

given v, b, r, k, lambda : int(1..)

where v * r = b * k,
      lambda * (v - 1) = r * (k - 1)

find design : matrix indexed by [int(1..b)] of set (size k) of int(1..v)

such that
    forAll point : int(1..v) .
        (sum i : int(1..b) . toInt(point in design[i])) = r,
    forAll p1 : int(1..v) . forAll p2 : int(p1+1..v) .
        (sum i : int(1..b) . toInt(p1 in design[i] /\ p2 in design[i])) = lambda,
    $ Symmetry breaking: order blocks by characteristic vector (allows duplicates)
    forAll i : int(1..b-1) .
        [toInt(j in design[i]) | j : int(1..v)] <=lex
        [toInt(j in design[i+1]) | j : int(1..v)]
